signifcant coefficient

R^2 suggests the model explains 49.3% of variance in explaining price

  • residuals vs fitted - indicates population sample is independent
  • normal q-q - skewed towards end of plot - suggests it plot is skewed
  • scale-location - there is heteroskedasticity in the residuals indicated by positive gradient and shape of the distribution of points

model suggests that waterfront (overlooking) has the greatest impact on price. We can say that a one unit increase in waterfront is associated with a 7.455 unit increase in price, holding all other factors constant

interaction: would probably choose, given bedrooms, what impact does sqft_living have on price?
